gin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10px; line-height: 0;\\\">[<a target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\\\" class=\\\"external text\\\" href=\\\"https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/converter.html?iso=20200912T12080000&amp;p1=137&amp;p2=1243&amp;p3=64&amp;p4=179&amp;p5=136&amp;p6=195&amp;p7=248&amp;p8=152\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: initial; text-decoration: var(--theme-link-decoration); transition: color 0.3s; line-height: inherit;\\\">TZ</a>]</sup>&nbsp;She was the first member of hololive -Myth- to debut. She performed the premiere of her first original rap song, \\\"失礼しますが、RIP♡\\\" or known in English as \\\"<a target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\\\" class=\\\"external text\\\" href=\\\"https://youtu.be/5y3xh8gs24c\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: initial; text-decoration: var(--theme-link-decoration); transition: color 0.3s; line-height: inherit;\\\">Excuse My Rudeness, But Could You Please RIP?</a>.\\\" The song was released on her YouTube channel the same day.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-17\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; unicode-bidi: isolate; text-wrap: nowrap; font-size: 10px; line-height: 0;\\\"><a href=\\\"https://virtualyoutuber.fandom.com/wiki/Mori_Calliope#cite_note-17\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: initial; text-decoration: var(--theme-link-decoration); transition: color 0.3s; line-height: inherit;\\\">[17]</a></sup><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-18\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; unicode-bidi: isolate; text-wrap: nowrap; font-size: 10px; line-height: 0;\\\"><a href=\\\"https://virtualyoutuber.fandom.com/wiki/Mori_Calliope#cite_note-18\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; verti